---
tracker:
  kind: linear
  api_key: $LINEAR_API_KEY
  project_slug: "__LINEAR_PROJECT_SLUG__"
  active_states:
    - Todo
    - In Progress
  terminal_states:
    - Done
    - Closed
    - Cancelled
    - Canceled
    - Duplicate

workspace:
  root: $SYMPHONY_WORKSPACES_ROOT

hooks:
  after_create: |
    rm -rf ./* ./.[!.]* 2>/dev/null || true
    git clone --depth 1 "__CLONE_URL__" . || {
      git clone --depth 1 "__CLONE_URL__" repo
      bash -c 'shopt -s dotglob && mv repo/* repo/.git .' 2>/dev/null
      rm -rf repo
    }

agent:
  max_concurrent_agents: 1
  max_turns: 20
  auto_stop_when_idle: true
  idle_grace_checks: 2

codex:
  command: 'CODEX_HOME="$SYMPHONY_CODEX_HOME" codex --model gpt-5.4 --config shell_environment_policy.inherit=all --config model_reasoning_effort=medium app-server'
  approval_policy: never
  thread_sandbox: workspace-write
---

You are working on Linear issue {{ issue.identifier }}.

Title: {{ issue.title }}

Body:
{{ issue.description }}

{% if attempt > 1 %}
This is retry attempt {{ attempt }}. A previous worker did not complete the issue cleanly.
Read the workspace and Linear comments before continuing, then focus on the remaining work.
{% endif %}

## Required behavior

- Read the repository `AGENTS.md` chain before making changes.
- Use repo-local guidance when relevant.
- Keep changes bounded to the issue.
- Run the issue validation commands before concluding work.
- Leave concise status updates and blockers in Linear.
- Treat `## Acceptance Criteria` as hard gates.
- Treat `## Validation Commands` as exact commands to run from repo root.
- Treat `## Touched Areas` as the expected scope. Note any extra files in the final comment.
- Post a final status comment before changing issue state.
- Expect most planned work to live in `Backlog` until the orchestrator activates it.
- Move successful issues to `In Review`, not directly to `Done`.
- Treat `In Review` as the orchestrator review gate.
- If you cannot complete the issue, move it back to `Todo` or a blocked state and explain why.
